# Bilingual content rules

> Terminology policy: [`non-negotiable-rules.mdc`](./non-negotiable-rules.mdc) § Terminology policy.
> All user-visible strings: `src/config/translations.js`.

- English and Arabic must match in meaning.
- One language must not make stronger claims.
- Preserve natural GCC/Arab commercial wording — not English-shaped Arabic.
- Use approved terminology for **reference price**, **retail quote**, **making charge**, and freshness labels (`live`, `updated`, `cached`, `delayed`).
- When fixing a mismatch, suggest exact EN/AR rewrite pairs — not vague “improve translation” notes.
- RTL layouts must work at 360px minimum.
